Worker fell from ladder: seriously injured
When replacing a defective outside probe crashed on Thursday a 51-year-old worker in eggelsberg from a ladder and was seriously injured.
The man from Lamprechtshausen wanted to replace on the facade of an inn a defective heater sensor.
When he rose to the ajar to the gutter ladder, ladder slipped and the man fell to the concrete floor.
He suffered serious injuries and was taken by helicopter "Christophorus 6" in the Salzburg Federal Hospital.
